Endometriosis of the bowel. One hundred sixty-three cases of endometriosis of the bowel (5.4% of 3037 laparotomies for endometriosis at the Ochsner Foundation Hospital) were reviewed to assess the management of this complication. Colon and rectal surgeons performed bowel resections of the colon in 30 cases and resections of the ileum and/or cecum in 11 cases. Gynecologic surgeons resected bowel implants, often multiple, in 153 patients, and also performed other necessary surgery, either ablative (with removal of uterus, tubes, and one or both ovaries 58.8%) or conservative (with preservation of reproductive potential